Package: brain-os-ai
Version: 1.0.0
Section: robotics
Priority: optional
Architecture: arm64
Depends: python3 (>= 3.11), libgrpc++-dev, libprotobuf-dev, protobuf-compiler-grpc, python3-grpcio, python3-protobuf, python3-websockets, python3-pydantic, python3-structlog
Recommends: nvidia-cuda-toolkit, tensorrt
Maintainer: Brain OS Team <dev@brain-os.local>
Homepage: https://github.com/brain-os/brain-os
Description: Brain OS AI — Cognitive engine for humanoid robotics
 Brain OS is a humanoid robot operating system that translates
 natural language instructions into robot execution.
 .
 This package provides the Python AI cognitive engine including:
  - LLM-based intent parsing and task decomposition (Qwen2.5-7B)
  - Multi-strategy trajectory generation (5 strategies)
  - Perception pipeline (YOLOv11 + ORB-SLAM3 + SAM2 + 3DGS)
  - Human-in-the-loop (HITL) management
  - Knowledge system (SQLite experience store + FAISS vector retrieval)
  - WebSocket event streaming
  - gRPC server for core engine integration
 .
 Target hardware: Jetson Orin with NVIDIA GPU
